headline.main: U.S.-VICHY PARLEYS HELD STILL DELICATE; Possible Departure of Leahy Is Weighed by Berne Observers

lead_paragraph: BERNE, Switzerland, Feb. 28 -- Despite favorable construction placed on dispatches from Washington, some foreign circles here consider that "explanations" between the Vichy and Washington governments are by no means at an end and remain "delicate."
abstract: Berne circles believe U S-Vichy parleys are still delicate; fleet still under discussion; believed Amb Leahy may leave; departure of Latin-Amer diplomats held possible
